registry/assessments/a5-nl.json:35:    "headline": "a5-nl is a DECISIVE, INSTRUMENT-VALID coverage FAIL of the deterministic NL front-end on the code vertical that ADDITIONALLY breaks the fail-closed contract — the DANGEROUS kind of failure, and the load-bearing contrast with its family/world sibling. Machinery leg [MEASURED]: over the SAME frozen eval queries, the gold-parse arm reproduced the parent-perfect result in-run (gold_replication_identical true; 855/855) and the deranged-lexicon control collapsed to 0.0 (G5) — the engine, kot_code desugaring, renderer, and scorer all work; the closed kot-query-code/1 grammar is decidable exactly as banked. NL-boundary leg [MEASURED]: routed through the deterministic a1-hybrid front-end, the same queries reach a correct, engine-answered, exact result on only 356 of 855 blind NL phrasings = 41.6% (one-sided Wilson 95% UB 0.4443 vs the frozen 0.90 retention bar), so the FAIL leg (UB <= 0.90) fires cleanly — the NL boundary eats roughly 58% of the rung. Fail-closed leg [MEASURED]: the S2 dangerous-wrong-answer KILL ALSO fired independently — covered wrong 43/855 = 5.0% (Wilson LB 0.0394 >= the 0.02 kill floor, 43 >= the 24-item fire threshold), so a5-nl has TWO independent FAIL causes, not one. The wrong answers are concentrated exactly where the design flagged the weak seat: contained-in (24/201 wrong) and where-defined (18/201 wrong) — the directional containment/definition-location families where the frame layer's ROLE_DIR direction table mis-parses 'what contains X' vs 'what X contains' into a valid-but-WRONG location answered with provenance attached. The call-graph families, by contrast, parse near-ceiling (callers-of 69/74, callees-of 60/73). Notably the CONTROL fail-closed is good (S1: 104/106 acceptable-refusal, holm_s1_pass true) — a5-nl refuses out-of-scope queries well but MIS-ANSWERS in-scope covered queries, the opposite profile from l3a-parse (which mis-handles some controls but keeps covered mis-parses safe). Net for the correctness thesis: the deterministic training-free NL front-end does NOT survive the natural-language boundary on the code vertical AND breaks its safety contract there; the frozen kill routes verbatim — 'fix the parser stage, not the narrative, and spend nothing on GPU for this leg' — with the frame stage indicted (frame-miss 468 dominant).",
registry/assessments/a5-nl.json:39:    "scope_envelope": "The envelope is the frozen extrapolation_envelope_verbatim, restated honestly. WHAT THIS FAIL ESTABLISHES: on the full 855-query frozen slice of the closed kot-query-code/1 grammar (code vertical, one 15-file Python snapshot), the ONE pinned deterministic a1-hybrid front-end build does not retain 90% of gold-parse covered exactness from THESE blind held-out NL phrasings AND breaks the fail-closed contract (wrong-answer rate above the 0.02 dangerous floor). It indicts the frame stage. WHAT IT DOES NOT GENERALIZE TO: (a) NO other mapper, gazetteer, or frame build — this is an a1-hybrid-specific result and the pre-declared successor (FK-NLB-3) is an LLM-assisted parser, a DIFFERENT front-end class the kill routes investment to; (b) NO other codebase or programming language, NO other phrasing distribution, NO natural-user-distribution robustness claim (phrasings agent-authored under a blind protocol); NO extraction-soundness claim w.r.t. runtime semantics (ASM-0009 unchanged); (c) NO LLM-comparative accuracy or cost claim (a5-llm / a5-llm-frontier), NO statement about kernel usefulness to any model; (d) NO cross-vertical conjunction — l3a-parse licenses the family/world vertical separately, and its fail-closed OUTCOME is the OPPOSITE (its S2 KILL did not fire), so the safety reading must stay strictly per-vertical; (e) it does NOT indict the kernel, the engine, or the closed grammar — the gold path replicates perfectly (855/855), so this is a boundary/front-end result, not a decidability result. A decisive FAIL is not softened (41.6% with UB 0.44, plus a fired safety kill), and a scoped FAIL is not over-generalized (it kills the a1-hybrid front-end at this slice, not the NL boundary in principle).",
registry/assessments/a5-nl.json:52:      "[ENVELOPE-BOUND] NO other codebase or programming language, NO other phrasing distribution, NO natural-user-distribution robustness claim; NO extraction-soundness claim w.r.t. runtime semantics (ASM-0009); NO LLM-comparative accuracy or cost claim (a5-llm / a5-llm-frontier). R0 throughout, 1 rung, scale language: none.",
registry/assessments/l3a-parse.json:34:    "headline": "l3a-parse is a DECISIVE, INSTRUMENT-VALID coverage FAIL of the deterministic NL front-end on the family/world vertical, wrapped around a clean machinery PASS — and it is the SAFE kind of failure: the front-end refuses far more than it errs. Machinery leg [MEASURED]: over the SAME frozen eval queries, the gold-parse arm reproduced the parent-perfect result in-run (gold_replication_identical true; 527/527 on the in-scope slice) and the deranged-lexicon control collapsed to 0.0 (G5) — the engine, renderer, and scorer all work; the closed kot-query/1 grammar is decidable exactly as banked. NL-boundary leg [MEASURED]: routed through the deterministic a1-hybrid front-end, the same in-scope queries reach a correct, engine-answered, exact result on only 251 of 527 blind NL phrasings = 47.6% (one-sided Wilson 95% UB 0.5121 vs the frozen 0.90 retention bar), so the FAIL leg (UB <= 0.90) fires cleanly — the NL boundary eats roughly 52% of the rung. Fail-closed leg [MEASURED]: the S2 dangerous-wrong-answer KILL did NOT fire (covered wrong 8/527 = 1.5%, Wilson LB 0.0086 < the 0.02 kill floor) — mis-parses on the family/world vertical overwhelmingly become REFUSALS (268/527 refused: 212 front-end ERR_PARSE + 56 safe engine refusals), not confident wrong answers. The fail-closed contract is imperfect but holds on the safety-critical direction: the 8 wrong answers are all parent-relation mis-picks in unique-father (6) / unique-mother (2), and the S2 Holm PASS gate (needs <=4) is missed, but the dangerous-wrong KILL threshold (~16+) is not reached. Net for the correctness thesis: the deterministic training-free NL front-end does NOT survive the natural-language boundary at the tested scope on the family/world vertical, and the frozen kill routes the consequence verbatim — 'L3 waits for a better parser, not more GPU'; the indicted stage is the frame layer (frame-miss 228 dominant across the stage breakdown).",
registry/assessments/truthstyle-2x2.json:37:      "[MEASURED] Instrument facts with standing value: the judges strongly separate correct from wrong content on BOTH tiers (tier-1 kernel-free external gold truth effect 0.804; tier-2 kernel-bytes truth effect 0.638), the style manipulation was real (0.94/1.00 fidelity), labels are stable (retest 0.9306, disclosed as a temperature-0 floor, not judge-quality evidence), and escapes were essentially unused (only cell rate: t2:wrong:plain 0.0033). The 2x2 factorial adjudication machinery itself (blind stateless invocations, pinned per-judge order, mandatory escape, per-attempt validity gates) executed 2424 planned invocations to 100% label coverage across two vendors and three models.",
registry/assessments/m0a-llmproxy.json:42:    "what_the_numbers_say": "Four separable measured facts, all proxy-estimand-scoped. (1) PRECISION IS THE STORY: under the blind cross-vendor judge, ~29% of mapped-strata decisions were judged wrong-sense (concept 31/100, prime 28/100 incorrect), against ~18% under the non-blind agent. Per-item agreement between the two judges on mapped strata is only 0.81/0.80 — about 1 in 5 items flips between them — so the two passes genuinely disagree at the item level; this is not a rounding difference [MEASURED: analysis-output agent_agreement_by_stratum]. (2) THE STRICT/LENIENT DUALITY COLLAPSED: proxy strict == lenient on both P and R because the judge issued ZERO 'unclear' labels over 200 mapped-strata items (the agent issued 11). The blind judge is maximally decisive; 'unclear' carried no mass, so the strict/lenient pair carries no information in the proxy pass, and comparisons against the agent's lenient numbers should not be made. (3) RECALL MOVED ONLY VIA ABSTAIN-MISS: 23/50 abstain items (0.46, vs agent 0.36) were judged to have a correct candidate the mapper declined — a recall/coverage cost (the mapper maps less than it defensibly could), not a correctness alarm. (4) THE NONE STRATUM HELD: 0/50 should-map judgments on the stratum covering 78% of token mass — the loudest possible alarm (a nonzero none-miss) did NOT fire, and the pre-existing thin-coverage discipline stands unchanged: R-LB95 0.6349 is driven by the Clopper-Pearson upper bound on a 50-item sample, i.e. by sampling thinness, not by any observed miss [STIPULATED: ASM-0542 — the proxy fixes NONE of the sampling design].",
registry/assessments/m0a-llmproxy.json:44:    "favourable_case_caveats_intact": "Everything above sits inside the parent design's own limits, all pre-registered and untouched by the proxy [STIPULATED: ASM-0542; envelope clause 3 verbatim: 'DESIGN LIMITS CARRY OVER UNCHANGED']: TinyStories is the pre-registered FAVOURABLE-CASE domain ('semantically clean 1.5k-word domain... near-exact mapping by construction'), so 0.71 precision here bounds nothing about harder domains except by the a-fortiori reading (a favourable-case number this size is more concerning, not less); stratum-population reweighting is stipulated from the published report; the none stratum is 50 items over 2,958,417 tokens; and the WSD-competence gap [envelope clause 2] means the LLM's sense judgments approximate human annotation with unproven offsets concentrated exactly where the agent pass located the error mass (light-verb, phrasal, idiomatic, auxiliary uses).",
registry/assessments/m0a-llmproxy.json:57:      "[DESIGN-BOUND] No statement about token-mass coverage, corpus engagement, or any E1 OUTCOME: this record measured an annotation instrument over pinned mapper outputs — it is not a lift, not a transfer result, and moves no E-series hypothesis. The E1 connection is risk-disclosure on inputs (ASM-0649), nothing more.",
registry/assessments/m0a-llmproxy.json:79:    {"stub_id": "shadowed-policy-blind-check", "question": "GENERALISED CAUTION from this record's finding: the AMENDMENT A1 shadowed-concept policy (docs/poc-design.md — sense-priority tiers for {inside, near, broken}, sense-correct 100%/100%/86%, ~129 declared wrong-sense tokens, feeding E1's 52-concept set) rests on the SAME species of non-blind agent-judged samples that this proxy just downgraded by ~0.11 on the main sample. Run the same blind-proxy protocol over those per-concept samples (or fold them into the human pass) before E1 shard builds treat 100%/100%/86% as solid.", "kind": "instrument", "est_cost_usd": 8, "est_agent_days": 1, "blocking": ["confidence in E1's declared wrong-sense token count"], "note": "requires its own prereg + fresh id; the human audit for these samples is already flagged pending in the A1 text (bead dix)"},
