registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:32:  "_surprise_note": "No prereg claim / registered prior exists (pre-freeze gating census), so no surprise-* tag is licensed. The registered sizing expectation ASM-0464 (EXTRAPOLATION, load-bearing for nothing) is CONFIRMED IN DIRECTION on limb (a): value concentrates in non-English high-fertility cells and English sits near the floor - now MEASURED on our pinned tokenizers, superseding the memory-tagged literature note. Limb (b) (material m-hat discount) is NOT resolved either way: the measured m-hat delta is tiny only because the estimator is a near-no-op upper bound (see flag-1 ratification), not because mappability risk is small.",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:35:    "headline": "A-E2 establishes, as a MEASURED-exploratory membership UPPER BOUND, that idea A's selection-stage value pool is real and large: at the 10k-concept K-A2 anchor the blended prefill-savings bound spans ~4.8% (harshest lawful cell: Qwen2.5 tokenizer, English-dominant usage-share weights, wordlike universe, m-hat, lower bracket) to ~43.6% (SmolLM2, uniform weights, all-surfaces, upper bracket); under the sub-methods ratified below the decision-facing headline is blended uniform wordlike membership @10k = 33.4-41.7% (SmolLM2, lower/upper bracket) and 18.5-24.0% (Qwen2.5). The value is fertility-asymmetry-driven and concentrates overwhelmingly in non-English cells (fi @10k 38.7-44.3%, ja 18.0-56.7% across tokenizers, wordlike); English alone is near the floor (mean BPE/word ~1.15, en @10k wordlike 3.9-5.9%). K-A2 does NOT fire anywhere on the grid (interpretive: minimum upper bracket @10k = 7.06% >= the 5% STIPULATED floor, and K-A2 may fire only off the upper bracket per ASM-0462). This is a stark, like-for-like-tier contrast with the parked idea B (~0.4% word-mass savings, ~5x BELOW its floor, at the same census tier): idea A is ALIVE at the selection stage, and the first efficiency-thesis breadth number of this magnitude in the programme. It is ONLY a membership upper bound: mappability (K-A4) is unpriced in every cell, the consumption channel (K-A3 tokenizer-extension null, trained-compressor null, 1-token-per-concept delivery, accuracy non-inferiority) is entirely unmeasured, and the bound must never be quoted as achievable savings.",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:39:      "read": "DOES NOT FIRE. Per ASM-0462 the kill may fire only off the UPPER bracket; the minimum upper bracket @10k across the full 16-cell grid (2 tokenizers x 2 weight arms x 2 m-hat modes x 2 surface filters) is 7.06% (Qwen2.5 | usage-share | m-hat | wordlike), i.e. every cell's kill-side number clears the floor. Most of the decision-facing grid clears it by 3-8x (uniform wordlike upper brackets: SmolLM2 41.7%, Qwen 24.0%).",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:40:      "harshest_cell": "Qwen2.5 | usage-share | m-hat | wordlike @10k = 4.79% lower / 7.06% upper. The 5% floor falls BETWEEN the brackets in this one cell: it can neither fire the kill (upper >= floor) nor support a go (lower < floor). Per ASM-0462's between-brackets clause this conditionally forces A-F1 (cross-lingual alignment) design BEFORE any mint decision - binding if and only if the freeze-time consumption currency is a high-CJK-coverage Qwen-like tokenizer AND the ratified workload mix is English-dominant. It does not block A-F0 (ASM-0463: A-F0 survives even a K-A2 fire).",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:45:      "[MEASURED-exploratory] Selection-stage value pool: on the ASM-0461-pinned inputs, minting 10k concepts by the value(c) objective bounds blended prefill savings at 33.4-41.7% (SmolLM2, uniform, wordlike, membership, lower/upper bracket) and 18.5-24.0% (Qwen2.5, same cell) - one to two orders of magnitude above the parked idea B's measured ~0.4% at the same census tier. Scope: membership upper bound, these two tokenizers, these four wordfreq lists, listed-word running text (~99% of list mass; unlisted tail excluded from numerator AND denominator).",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:46:      "[MEASURED-exploratory] Fertility asymmetry is real on OUR pinned tokenizers (no longer a memory-tagged literature claim): mean BPE/word en 1.16/1.15 (SmolLM2/Qwen), es 1.85/1.41, fi 3.15/2.68, ja 3.06/1.34; per-language @10k membership (all-filter) en 10.6%/9.3%, es 37.0%/20.4%, fi 46.3%/41.0%, ja 57.5%/19.7%. English contributes near-floor value by construction (most high-frequency English words are already 1 token). This resolves ASM-0464 limb (a) in direction, superseding the unverified literature note for these tokenizers.",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:47:      "[MEASURED-exploratory] Strong tokenizer dependence: SmolLM2 tokenizes Japanese ~2.3x more expensively than Qwen2.5 (ja mean BPE/word 3.06 vs 1.34; ja @10k 57.5% vs 19.7%), because Qwen's vocabulary has far more CJK coverage. The consumption currency (which host tokenizer denominates savings; ASM-0103 / A-E3) is therefore load-bearing for any freeze-time margin on this track.",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:56:      "[NOT ACHIEVABLE SAVINGS] The bound assumes every minted concept is delivered in exactly 1 token, losslessly consumed, with zero accuracy cost. The entire consumption channel is unmeasured: the K-A3 tokenizer-vocabulary-extension null (just extend the tokenizer, no kernel needed) and the trained-compressor null are LIVE downstream kills that census cannot settle (ASM-0460); accuracy non-inferiority is an F3-stage co-primary. Quoting these percentages as deliverable efficiency gains is an overclaim.",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:57:      "[ENVELOPE-BOUND] Scope is these 4 languages, these 2 tokenizers, wordfreq-3.1.1 large lists, and listed-word running text. The blended numbers extrapolate to no other workload, tokenizer, or language mix; the usage-share arm is STIPULATED-exploratory, not a measured mix (ASM-0561); renormalising the raw web-share inputs over only 4 languages concentrates 0.832 weight on English and omits the ~1/3 of web content in other (mostly non-English, fertility-bearing) languages - a full mix would likely land between the two arms, but that is unmeasured.",
registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:80:      {"claim": "cross-lingual BPE fertility asymmetry (non-English words cost multiple tokens where English is ~1) on the programme's pinned host tokenizers", "from": "EXTRAPOLATION (ASM-0464 limb a; memory-tagged literature note, unverified)", "to": "MEASURED-exploratory", "scope": "SmolLM2-135M + Qwen2.5-0.5B tokenizers, wordfreq-3.1.1 en/es/fi/ja lists"},
