registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json:131:  "tree_impact": "crosslingual-phrase-coverage (idea A) mini-tree: A-E2 rung COMPLETE and POSITIVE at the membership-upper-bound tier - mechanism_state = alive-selection-stage; K-A2 interpretively clear everywhere on the kill-side bracket; next rung = A-F0 (mint economics, ~$5-10, pre-cleared, condition 'after the A-E2 readout' now satisfied); A-E1 stays gated (ASM-0463) and additionally acquires the K-A4-pricing prerequisite (ASM-0560) and the conditional A-F1 prerequisite (ASM-0563). The A-E3/consumption-currency question is promoted from housekeeping to load-bearing by the measured 2-3x tokenizer dependence. Idea B (parked, ASM-0460): unchanged - but A-E2's fi/ja fertility measurements strengthen the case that coverage growth (B's re-entry lever) is best bought cross-lingually. Efficiency-thesis breadth: this is the programme's first measured multi-tens-of-percent efficiency bound on any input-compression mechanism; it is an upper bound and must be consumed as such. Nothing frozen, nothing spent, no verdict object created; census remains quarantined MEASURED-exploratory."
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:28:    "scope_note": "Every number in this assessment: SmolLM2-1.7B-Instruct pinned commit 31b70e2e869a7173562077fd711b654946d38674, zero-shot, CLUTRR entity form 2, the 958-item covered set (third disclosed patched-probe contact, ASM-0402), fp32 chat template, additive norm-matched contrastive injection at the final prompt-token position, greedy max_new_tokens=16, n=200 swept failures (= full F) per unit, 3 derangement seeds, phase:exploratory. Citing any of them wider re-classifies the citation as EXTRAPOLATION."
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:35:    "headline": "Stage-1 is INCONCLUSIVE on a VALID instrument, and the reading licensed by the spec's own pre-fixed boundaries is two-sided and must be kept two-sided. Side one, re-confirmed: the internal-write channel DELIVERS at echo grade - keying replicated exactly at alpha=1.0 (keyacc_real 0.810/0.850 at (12,16)/(16,16), the same point values B2P measured, UB95 0.8514/0.8868 far above the 0.70 replication floor, now against THREE independent derangement seeds) [MEASURED-exploratory: poc/nsk1/out/stage1/stage1_summary.json sha256 63525fcd...; offline recount exact]. Side two, the probe's actual question, UNRESOLVED: whether that delivered content INTEGRATES into free generation. The echo-proof endpoint R- (rescue under the true-fact minus sign, which echo cannot pass) fired at ZERO of 8 units and sits at-or-below the content-free coin null everywhere (real 0.040-0.125 across the ladder vs coin 0.035-0.240; mean delta vs coin negative at all 8 units; pooled UB95 <= 0.0384 everywhere, versus the 0.10 kill bound) - yet the run is NOT a KILL, because the pre-declared KILL label is a both-endpoints-times-all-8-units conjunction and the echo-confounded R+ endpoint at alpha=1.0 exceeds the kill bound at both cells (pooled UB95 0.1423/0.1390; mean delta vs coin +0.075/+0.078; per-seed coin p down to 3.6e-4 but not < 0.00625 at all three seeds; delta floors unmet). What blocks a clean negative is therefore a sub-floor, echo-confounded, delivered-conclusion residual - not any positive trace on the integration endpoint. Why this does not settle integration negatively either: (a) no per-endpoint KILL label was pre-declared, so no 'integration killed' statement exists to mint; (b) constructively, the R- bound is a NET bound under ASM-0404's deliberately conservative sign semantics - the minus-sign write simultaneously delivers the true fact AND pushes the bridge SURFACE against the gold answer (measured on this run's own C100 frontier: minus-sign breakage 32/34 per 100 at alpha=1.0 with 27/26 of the breaks emitting the bridge name), so 'no integration' and 'integration cancelled by the operator's own anti-gold surface push' are not separated by this design at ANY n; and (c) the R+ residual is consistent with both echo and weak integration, and by construction can never license the integration reading. Net: the internal-write channel is deliverable at echo grade (replicated), and its integration into free generation is UNRESOLVED - bounded near zero NET under this operator, unmeasured under any operator that de-confounds fact delivery from answer-surface push. One further measured novelty: the keying-vs-damage frontier came back co-attenuating - below alpha=1.0 keying decays into the role band (0.685/0.625 at 0.75; 0.54-0.63 at 0.5; 0.54-0.56 at 0.25, vs role 0.505-0.615) while breakage decays in step (32-34% -> 4-5%), so NO strength window exists on this ladder where keying is strong and damage is low.",
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:45:      "keying_frontier": "keyacc_real by unit: 0.810/0.850 (alpha=1.0), 0.685/0.625 (0.75), 0.630/0.540 (0.5), 0.560/0.540 (0.25) vs role 0.505-0.615 and coin 0.455-0.570 throughout. Keying exists cleanly only at alpha=1.0; by alpha<=0.5 it is inside the control band. C100 breakage co-attenuates: minus 32/34 -> 17/13 -> 8/6 -> 4/4 per 100 (bridge-name emission among minus-breaks 27/26 -> 13/8 -> 5/5 -> 3/3), plus 16/13 -> 13/9 -> 5/4 -> 1/1; collapse 0-2 everywhere. Keying and damage rise and fall TOGETHER on this operator.",
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:52:      "TIGHT NET BOUND ON THE ECHO-PROOF ENDPOINT: R- (rescue under the true-fact minus sign) is at-or-below the content-free coin null at every unit (mean delta vs coin -0.050 to -0.010; never beats role either), with pooled UB95 <= 0.0384 everywhere measured - the NET content-specific integration-rescue increment under THIS operator is bounded well below the 0.10 campaign floor, and below 0.05, at every (cell, alpha) on the frontier. Scope-critical qualifier carried from ASM-0404: this is a NET bound under a sign semantics whose surface push works AGAINST gold; it is not a pure integration null [MEASURED-exploratory: unit_reports + recount].",
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:64:      "NOT safety: the frontier finding is adverse - no measured strength window separates keying from damage on this operator (plus-sign breakage is still 9-13% at alpha=0.75 where keying is already marginal).",
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:79:      "recommended": "ACCEPT-INCONCLUSIVE-AND-RECORD (rank 1): close the flagship internal-steering arc with the two-stage ledger as measured - B2P: delivery POSITIVE at echo grade; Stage-1: delivery REPLICATED, integration UNRESOLVED with tight net bounds on the echo-proof endpoint and a sub-floor echo-confounded residual on the other - and return the flagship's delivery-topology weight to engine-external designs (the K-NULL ablation and the human f2b-transfer adjudication remain the highest-value open items in the synthesis). WHY NOT the higher-powered rescue probe: (a) there is NO measured positive integration effect size to power against - R- is at-or-below coin everywhere, so a bigger run of this construct powers up a bound already tight; (b) the only positive trend (R+ ~ +0.075) cannot license integration at ANY n by the pre-fixed ASM-0404 boundary, and design-time arithmetic (not evidence) puts even ITS per-seed 0.00625 conjunct at ~n>=540 discordance-adjusted - while the corpus failure population is EXHAUSTED at 200, so added power means new items, a fourth disclosed contact, and heavier freeze burden, all to confirm at best an emission-only label; (c) the run answered the frontier question negatively (keying and damage co-attenuate), removing the cheap-win hypothesis that a lower alpha preserves keying safely. IF the maintainer wants the internal-integration question kept alive (rank 2, conditional): the next spend is a NEW OPERATOR/READ-OUT DESIGN, not a re-run - one that de-confounds fact delivery from answer-surface push (e.g. inject the hop-1 fact FRAME without a name-slot push, or multi-position/earlier-position delivery, or read-out-placement designs), specced fresh with its own gates, per-endpoint kill labels pre-declared, >= 3 derangement seeds, and the fourth corpus contact disclosed. That is the only design class that can separate 'no integration' from 'integration masked by this operator'.",
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:89:  "mechanism_state": "internal residual-stream channel: POSITIVE-ECHO-GRADE-REPLICATED for delivery (keyacc 0.810/0.850 at alpha=1.0, twice, 3 seeds, tripwires clean) / INTEGRATION-INCONCLUSIVE (echo-proof rescue endpoint at-or-below the content-free null everywhere, pooled UB95 <= 0.0384, under a conservative anti-gold sign semantics; echo-confounded endpoint sub-floor positive at alpha=1.0 only); keying-vs-damage frontier: co-attenuating, no low-damage keying window on this operator; text-delivery comparator: unchanged (dead with measured mechanism, g2d); engine-external verification: unchanged (f2b positive, correct-alignment-specific, confounded, audited); 360M-few-shot second rung: stays parked (its unlock condition - Stage-1 integration evidence - did not arrive)",
registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json:123:  "tree_impact": "nsk1 stays DRAFT/unfrozen; the internal-steering measurement ARC (B-prime -> B2P -> Stage-1) is CLOSED with gate label INCONCLUSIVE and a complete two-stage ledger: delivery POSITIVE at echo grade and REPLICATED (0.810/0.850, twice, 3 seeds), integration UNRESOLVED (echo-proof endpoint bounded near zero NET under a conservative operator; echo-confounded residual sub-floor at alpha=1.0 only; no fire, no kill). The delivery-topology cell updates by qualification only - POSITIVE-ECHO-GRADE-REPLICATED / INTEGRATION-INCONCLUSIVE - neither 'helps generation' nor 'does not'. ASM-0342 is discharged; ASM-0500..0503 now govern citation, kill-attribution, the frontier reading, and successor sequencing. The flagship's critical path returns to the maintainer fork: record-and-redirect (engine-external topologies per the feasibility synthesis) or a new de-confounded operator spec. No verdict object exists anywhere in this line and nothing here may be cited as one; the programme's verdict-grade bottom line (zero audited end-task wins over the kernel-as-text null) is unchanged."
