registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json:28:    "scope_note": "Every number in this assessment: SmolLM2-1.7B-Instruct pinned commit 31b70e2e869a7173562077fd711b654946d38674, zero-shot, CLUTRR entity form 2, the 958-item covered set (ASM-0203 contact discipline), fp32 chat template, additive norm-matched contrastive injection at the final prompt-token position at alpha=1.0, teacher-forced paired logprob margins for the gate, n=200 swept failures per cell, phase:exploratory. Citing any of them wider re-classifies the citation as EXTRAPOLATION."
registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json:35:    "headline": "B2P is PASS-KEYED on a VALID instrument, and the interpretation licensed by the spec's own pre-fixed boundary is: content-specific internal steering EXISTS at R3 - a single-position additive residual-stream write at the final prompt token delivers ITEM-SPECIFIC content (which of two counterfactual names was injected) that the host's forward computation reads out, at 2 of 9 grid cells, beating both the arithmetic-chance coin control AND the role-consistent deranged control with FWER <= 0.05 [MEASURED-exploratory: poc/nsk1/out/bprime2/bprime2_summary.json sha256 0ee800f7f7d1aec0aa245986aa9a27a15017ebc33d5780a9cb4104da366f76f1; cells (12,16) keyacc_real 0.810, Wilson-LB(z=2.5427) 0.730, paired vs coin p=1.35e-10, vs role p=8.87e-07; (16,16) 0.850, LB 0.775, p=4.11e-13 / 9.06e-11; effect sizes m(+)-m(-): real +2.82/+2.80 vs role +0.59/+0.81 vs coin +0.10/-0.07, against a baseline unhooked margin of mean 0.62]. The role-control conjunct is what makes this ITEM-keyed rather than merely direction-keyed: the same deranged vector under the same fixed key-to-sign assignment moves margins only +0.6-0.8, so the signal tracks WHICH item's counterfactual pair was injected, not a generic top-vs-bridge direction. This is the FIRST positive delivery mode in the programme's delivery topology, and it lands in direct contrast to the text channel measured on the same items at the same host: the engine's fact delivered as prompt text was net-harmful with zero rescues (g2d: 0.76 -> 0.43, 0/24 rescued), while the same content class delivered as a contrastive residual write is cleanly readable. Delivery topology, not content, was the binding failure - now measured from both sides. Scope bound, fixed by the spec BEFORE the run and untouched here: PASS-KEYED establishes content DELIVERY (at least echo-grade readable content); whether the computation INTEGRATES it as grounding - rescuing real generations on real tasks - is Stage-1's question, and this record does not advance it.",
registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json:62:      "NOT damage-free: at the measured strength the write breaks 13-16% of correct free generations at the keying cells even under the helpful sign, and 32-34% under the adverse sign. The internal channel is measured READABLE, not measured SAFE; the strength-vs-damage frontier is Stage-1 work.",
registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json:78:      "recommended": "STAGE-1 FREE-GENERATION KEYED-RESCUE PROBE FIRST (rank 1), then the redesigned DRAFT record. The single largest inferential gap between this result and anything the flagship can use is teacher-forced-margin -> free-generation behaviour AT THE MEASURED KEYING CELLS - a gap this run cannot close because its generation secondaries were pivot-fixed at a dead cell. The designer should spec a bounded successor at cells (12,16) and (16,16) only (multiplicity 2, no new grid search): keyed emission + rescue-of-text-only-failures under real vs deranged-coin arms in free generation, an alpha ladder BELOW 1.0 (the keying-vs-damage frontier - does keying survive at alpha where the 13-16% plus-sign breakage does not?), >= 2 additional derangement seeds (single-seed robustness is the cheapest remaining attack), and the role arm carried as covariate. Same instrument family, same caps class (~USD 1-5 at measured throughput), phase:exploratory, fork-deciding only. WHY THIS ORDER: a rescue-positive makes the redesigned nsk1 record's rung logic and power real instead of extrapolated from margins; a rescue-negative (content readable but never integrated in generation) redirects Stage-1 toward read-out placement rather than a doomed campaign - either way the DRAFT record is written once, on measurements.",
registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json:91:    {"stub_id": "nsk1-stage1-freegen-spec", "question": "Designer: spec the Stage-1 free-generation keyed-rescue probe at cells (12,16) and (16,16) - keyed emission + rescue of text-only failures, real vs deranged-coin arms, alpha ladder below 1.0 (keying-vs-damage frontier), >= 2 additional derangement seeds, role arm as covariate, bounded multiplicity 2, phase:exploratory, caps class <= USD 25 (likely USD 1-5 at measured throughput).", "kind": "falsification", "est_cost_usd": 25, "est_agent_days": 1, "blocking": ["nsk1 redesign/refreeze", "flagship internal-vs-external question"]},
registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json:108:    {"id": "ASM-0112 (direction-only mechanism reading, discrete gold-hit read-outs)", "outcome": "resolved-by-circumvention per its own resolution path", "backing_ref": "B2P's margin read-out avoided the discrete gold-hit class entirely, and its operator contrast confirms the reading's usefulness: the same single-position final-token write that is source-blind under a discrete any-cell gold metric is cleanly source-KEYED under a paired continuous margin. The claim's measured core stands for discrete read-outs; its 'no usable signal from single-position injection' worry is now bounded to the read-out class, not the channel."},
registry/assessments/b-cov-define-lane.json:58:      "[READ, efficiency breadth] For the efficiency thesis this is the MEASURED breadth-zero counterpart to the substrate-ready 0.7710: substrate readiness did not translate to external breadth, exactly as the three-legs discipline predicted. It banks 'the define lane's external κ_B is currently ~0 on the biomedical Tier-A slice, and the binding gap is leg-3 template shape' — an honest, actionable breadth bound, not a mechanism kill."
registry/assessments/b-cov-define-lane.json:74:      "what_this_census_unlocks": "[READ] It closes the internal record's stub b-cov-define-slice with a MEASURED external endpoint and re-prioritises: the next informative move for define-lane breadth is NOT more internal counting (0.7710 already banked) and NOT endorsing more shards first — it is the leg-3 MAPPER TEMPLATE EXPANSION, because the parse histogram shows that gap dominates. WiC remains blocked on the data unblock (boundary-stop)."
