registry/assessments/a5-llm.json:87:    {"id": "ASM-0013 (faithful kernel-as-text + oracle-strong retrieval upper-bounds deployable RAG)", "outcome": "resolved-measured at pack level, QUALIFIED at delivery", "backing_ref": "/analysis/retrieval_completeness_violations=0 (mechanical); but truncation_counts 194/977 in every rag cell mean the delivered context under-ran the oracle-strong stipulation on 19.9% of items (design expected 0). The upper-bound reading survives for the PASS direction (truncation only depresses the null, and the worst-case repair bound cannot flip anything) but the rag cells' ABSOLUTE level is not the handed-facts ceiling. Still-open for long context -> a5-llm-frontier."},
registry/assessments/oracle-coverage.json:25:    "scope_note": "All three verdicts: rung R0 (no host model), scale_language_licensed: none. m0b coverage is corpus-indexed (pinned TinyStories task-family table, denominator 1,709,765 content-word tokens) and kernel-state-indexed (the incomplete kernel-v0 + molecules-v0 instance of 2026-07-08). l3a/a5 carry coverage: null BY DESIGN — their covered slices are authored against their own stores (coverage by construction), so no m0b-style gate applies and no fact-coverage claim exists. Extrapolation envelopes verbatim in each verdict are binding on every number quoted below."
