registry/assessments/oracle-coverage.json:36:      "mechanical_numbers": "coverage_fraction 0.3542001386155407 at primary rung molecules-v0, over the FULL census denominator 1,709,765 content-word tokens (605,599 covered; audit independently recomputed the exact fraction). Secondary by-rung: kernel-v0 0.2210, molecules-v0 0.3542, wn31-aligned 0.7841. Deterministic census, no sampling, no annotators, no statistical test (count-based criterion per P1 common rules; the non-top-500 tail counts as uncovered — the conservative direction).",
registry/assessments/oracle-coverage.json:38:      "kill_chain_read": "SUPPORTS (by not firing) the non-niche sub-claim at gate strength: the pre-registered consequence (NICHE-SCOPE banner on every verdict + mandatory coverage-growth cost line on frontier pitches) is not bound. It KILLS nothing and cannot: m0b is a gate-with-consequence, not a hypothesis. It does NOT support any general-coverage claim — the register's worked caution (ASM-0001/ASM-0002) exists precisely because this number was once narrated as 'natural coverage'; that promotion remains unlicensed and this assessment does not repeat it.",
