registry/assessments/oracle-coverage.json:128:  "tree_impact": "ORACLE+COVERAGE family after this assessment: all three leaves CLOSED as instrument/perimeter facts — m0b gate cleared (banner not bound; number banked with all indices; standing re-census gate), l3a engine leg certified, a5 code-vertical leg certified with byte-identical-engine portability and a demonstrated deterministic population route. The correctness thesis's deterministic-grounding case is now measured up to the fortress wall: sound, fail-closed, licensed, microsecond-cheap checking over kernel-governed records EXISTS (MEASURED, cross-vendor CONFIRMED, R0) — and every step that would make it matter to a model (NL parse in, LLM comparison, end-task lift over the kernel-as-text null) is an open pre-registered successor, not a licensed claim. No number in this batch may be quoted without its envelope: m0b's 0.3542 is corpus/rung/kernel-state-indexed; l3a/a5 exactness is against self-authored stores at R0. Fable interpretive assessment is DONE for m0b, l3a, a5. Coordinator actions (out of my scope): append the three audit-status lines; schedule successors per questions_opened."
registry/assessments/f-efficiency.json:61:      "kill_chain_read": "FAIL, landed as a FAIL. Fired rule index 1: gap_below_half OR competitor_closes_asmuch OR cost_ratio_vs_S >= 1. Mechanically: gap_below_half = true AND competitor_closes_asmuch = true (cost_ratio_vs_S = 0.4327 < 1, so leg (c) did not fire). The frozen HE1 primary — gap_closed_fraction(R1,R2) at best pre-registered retry budget — measured -40.13 (95% CI [-135.6, -23.1], primary_p 0.567): the pre-registered kill fired and HE1 in its (R1,R2) gap-closure form is DEAD as registered. No rescue is available or attempted: the frozen record cannot be amended post-final, and any follow-up needed a new id (which is exactly what f2b-replicate was). The DIAGNOSTIC read, which does not soften the verdict: the estimand's denominator was degenerate — R2-alone (360M) scored <= R1-alone (135M) on the D-QA slice (0.388 vs 0.394, descriptive cells from the post-mortem, bead kernel-of-truth-97r), so the s->S gap the fraction divides by was ~-0.006 and BOTH fired legs (a) and (b) are arithmetically contaminated by it: with no gap to close, 'closes <50% of the gap' and 'a competitor closes as much gap' are near-vacuous. The FAIL is therefore strongly informative about GAP-CLOSURE ESTIMAND DESIGN (a gap-existence instrument gate is mandatory — f2b-replicate's separation gate is the direct fix, and it validated: R3-R1 gap 0.108, LB 0.072 > 0) and only weakly informative about verifier-offload itself. That attribution is not speculation: it is the MEASURED finding of the audited f2b-replicate PASS (registry/assessments/f2b-replicate.json: 'the F2 primary's death is now attributable to its degenerate gap denominator, not to the absence of a lift, WITHIN THIS SCOPE'). Separately and UN-contaminated by the denominator: HE2 cascade-dominance FAILED its Holm-corrected pre-registered test (cascade_dominance = false, worst-budget p = 0.0471, Holm within F-secondary(f2)); per the verbatim HE2 kill ('Dead if not strictly dominant over BOTH the logprob gate AND the gloss-text self-check gate ... at every pre-registered escalation budget'), M5's cascade-dominance claim is DEAD at this scope — the cascades ran 135M->1.7B and do not inherit the R1/R2 degeneracy. HC3's commodity-verification kill did NOT fire (prm_beaten = true, p ~1e-4, unaudited; later re-confirmed under audit by f2b-replicate at the pinned 1.5B PRM class). HS12 carried no kill and no endpoint in the verdict object; no placement claim is made.",
registry/assessments/f-efficiency.json:66:        "[MEASURED-UNAUDITED, leakage-caveated] The pre-registered secondaries that passed, within scope: kernel verifier beats gloss-text self-verify+retry (p ~1e-4), beats the kernel-as-text null (p ~1e-4), beats the trained PRM at matched FLOPs (p ~1e-4, HC3 kill not fired), gap_closed(R2,R3) = 2.73 (p ~1e-4, the second frozen rung pair, where a real gap existed), seed-sign gate consistent (boolean true = >=4/5 seeds same-direction per the frozen test), cost_ratio_vs_S = 0.4327 < 1. These carry BOTH banners verbatim: (i) MEASURED-UNAUDITED (audit state N/A — negatives are not audit-gated), and (ii) the flagged oracle-leakage caveat — on D-QA the verifier's accept test is string-equality to the same canonical record that DEFINED the gold answer, so the measured lift is inflated by the eval's construction. Their properly-landed, audited successor is f2b-replicate's envelope-scoped PASS (+0.1507 absolute, LB +0.1053, shuffled-derangement control recovering ~0), which this record adopts by reference and does not restate beyond that.",
registry/assessments/f-efficiency.json:67:        "[MEASURED-UNAUDITED] Efficiency cost datum at this scope: cost_ratio_vs_S = 0.4327 (F0 ledger) — the verify-retry arm ran below half the per-query cost of model_S while the estimand around it degenerated. Consistent in direction with f2b-replicate's audited cost_ratio_vs_R3 = 0.103; neither number extends beyond its eval design."
